    "type": "spell",
    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">You implant a mental mine within your psyche that detonates against anyone attempting to manipulate your thoughts. You can use a single action, which has the concentrate trait, to suppress the effects of the mine for 1 round to allow someone to safely use a mental effect on you. You can Dismiss the spell.<br /><br />The first creature that uses a mental effect against you triggers the animus mine, causing the spell to end. The animus mine deals 4d8 mental damage to the triggering creature, which must attempt a Will save.<br /><br /><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.<br /><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.<br /><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.dfCMdR4wnpbYNTix]{Stunned} 1.<br /><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.dfCMdR4wnpbYNTix]{Stunned} 1. You are unaffected by the triggering mental effect.</span></p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+1)</strong> The damage increases by 2d8.&nbsp;</p>",
